## medichek (client package)

This folder holds the Python client package and helper files for the patient-side application.

Running client & server together

The simplest way to run the server and client in tandem is to open two PowerShell windows and run each component in its own virtual environment.

1) Start the server (in one PowerShell window):

```powershell
cd "c:\Users\songguopeng\Documents\projects\medichek project\medichek-server"
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py runserver 8000
```

2) Start the client (in a second PowerShell window):

```powershell
cd "c:\Users\songguopeng\Documents\projects\medichek project\medichek\medichek-client"
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m client_app.main
```

Optional: launch both in new windows from a script (one-liners). Replace paths if different on your machine.

```powershell
Start-Process powershell -ArgumentList '-NoExit','cd "c:\Users\songguopeng\Documents\projects\medichek project\medichek-server"; .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1; python manage.py runserver 8000'
Start-Process powershell -ArgumentList '-NoExit','cd "c:\Users\songguopeng\Documents\projects\medichek project\medichek\medichek-client"; .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1; python -m client_app.main'
```

Notes
- Server runs at http://127.0.0.1:8000 by default. The client stub contacts no server yet, but future work will POST session data and captures to the server API.
- If you change ports, update the client code or pass the server URL via environment variables or CLI.
a remote check in software for patients with medications
